{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Interval\n",
    "\n",
    "In these examples we will explore the interval embedding. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pylab as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.embed import IntervalEmbedding\n",
    "from wildboar.utils.plot import plot_time_domain\n",
    "\n",
    "random_state = 1234"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load a dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"CBF\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we define an interval embedding with a fixed non-overlapping amount of intervals, where each interval is summarized as its mean, variance and slope."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "fixed = IntervalEmbedding(n_interval=30, summarizer=\"auto\", intervals=\"fixed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We fit and transform the time series and extract the start index for each interval."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_t = fixed.fit_transform(x)\n",
    "labels = [\"%s\" % start for (dim, (start, length, _)) in fixed.embedding_.features]\n",
    "n_features = x_t.shape[1]\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we plot the time series and the mean, variance and slope respectivley."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=4, figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_time_domain(x, y=y, ax=ax[0], cmap=\"rainbow\")\n",
    "ax[0].title.set_text(\"Time series\")\n",
    "colors = plt.cm.rainbow(np.linspace(0, 1, 3))\n",
    "titles = [\"Mean\", \"Variance\", \"Slope\"]\n",
    "for i in range(3):\n",
    "    ax[i + 1].bar(labels, x_t[0, i:n_features:3], color=colors[i, :])\n",
    "    plt.setp(ax[i + 1].get_xticklabels(), rotation=\"vertical\", ha=\"center\")\n",
    "    ax[i + 1].title.set_text(titles[i])\n",
    "    ax[i + 1].set_xlim([0, 29])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot(p, var, labels, index):\n",
    "    colors = plt.cm.rainbow(np.linspace(0, 1, len(labels)))\n",
    "    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "    ax = fig.add_subplot(projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "    ax.scatter(p[:, 0], p[:, 1], p[:, 2], color=colors[index, :])\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"Component 1 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[0])\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"Component 2 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[1])\n",
    "    ax.set_zlabel(\"Component 3 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[2])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "labels, index = np.unique(y, return_inverse=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Similar to the other embeddings we use principal component analysis to explore the resulting embedding."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ie = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    IntervalEmbedding(\n",
    "        n_interval=100,\n",
    "        summarizer=\"auto\",\n",
    "        intervals=\"random\",\n",
    "        random_state=random_state,\n",
    "        n_jobs=-1,\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    PCA(n_components=3, random_state=random_state),\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot(ie.fit_transform(x), ie.steps[1][1].explained_variance_ratio_, labels, index)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  }
 ],
